      <div class="msgContentFrame">I've been leveling goldsmith these past few days, and it's not as hard as one might think. The best part about crafting thus far is the local levequest. Essentially, you pay nothing and are provided materials and crystals to make items for people, while obtaining lots of exp and items for your craft. Mining also provides the opportunity to dig up ores that you can turn into nuggets and then into items. Honestly, I find it no more challenging so far than any other craft I've attempted. As with all crafts, it takes time, patience, and the desire to gather your materials if you aren't filthy rich.<div class="msgSig"><div class="msgSigBar sm">----------------------------</div> <br /><div class="msgQuote"><div class="source">Quote:</div><div class="orig"> &quot;Me fail English? That's unpossible!&quot; -Ralph </div></div></div></div>
